# 📝 Problem Statement

Percentage is a way of expressing a number as a fraction of 100.

It is one of the most frequently asked topics in placement aptitude tests.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💡 Formula 1 – Find Percentage

Percentage = (Obtained Marks × 100) / Total Marks

### Example

Marks = 450

Total = 500

Percentage

= (450 × 100) / 500

= 90%

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💡 Formula 2 – Find Marks

Marks = (Percentage × Total Marks) / 100

### Example

Find 80% of 600

Marks

= (80 × 600) / 100

= 480

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 💡 Formula 3 – Find Total Marks

Total Marks = (Obtained Marks × 100) / Percentage

### Example

A student scored 450 marks which is 90%.

Total Marks

= (450 × 100) / 90

= 500

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

