# ⚡ Important Shortcuts

```text
50% = Divide by 2

25% = Divide by 4

20% = Divide by 5

10% = Divide by 10

5%  = Half of 10%

1%  = Divide by 100
```

Example

25% of 800

= 800 ÷ 4

= 200

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# 📚 Increase and Decrease

## Increase by Percentage

Formula

New Value = Original Value + Percentage of Original

Example

Increase ₹800 by 25%

25% of 800 = 200

New Value

800 + 200

= 1000

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## Decrease by Percentage

Formula

New Value = Original Value − Percentage of Original

Example

Decrease ₹1200 by 20%

20% of 1200 = 240

New Value

1200 − 240

= 960

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

